Now it&#39;s not finding the necessary bundled 3rd-party libraries.

I suggest you use the scripts in the heritrix /bin/ directory as a 
model; they set up the right classpath for including all necessary 
bundled libraries. In fact, even the script named &#39;heritrix&#39; can be used 
to launch other main classes (via the CLASS_MAIN environment variable) 
and in a foreground-mode (via the FOREGROUND environment variable), and 
the &#39;arcreader&#39; script is an example of doing that with the ARCReader 
class.

Separately, it&#39;s not the cause of your problems, but the Sun/Oracle JDK 
is usually the safest choice for running Heritrix, at least through 
JDK6. There have occasionally been obscure behavior/performance issues 
with OpenJDK (up through JDK6, where the code has a somewhat different 
pedigree and testing regime; I think the JDK7 versions are in much 
closer sync).

- Gordon

